    <lb n="1"/>Ἀφθονήτωι στρατη-

    <lb n="2"/>γῶι παρὰ Φιλίππου 

    <lb n="3"/>καὶ Πτολεμαίου. εἰσε-

    <lb n="4"/>δώκαμέν σοι ἔντευξιν 

    <lb n="5"/>κατὰ Παυσανίου περὶ 

    <lb n="6"/>ὧν ἐνεκαλοῦμεν αὐτῶι. 

    <lb n="7"/>σοῦ δὲ γράψαντος τῶι 

    <lb n="8"/>ἐπιστάτηι παραπέ-

    <lb n="9"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="high">μψαι αὐτὸν</supplied> <gap reason="illegible" extent="4" unit="character"/><gap reason="illegible" extent="2" unit="character"/> 

    <lb n="10"/>οὖ<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">ν</supplied> σε εἰσκαλέσασθαι 

    <lb n="11"/>ἡμᾶς καὶ ἐπισκεψά-

    <lb n="12"/>μενον ἃ διὰ τῆς ἐντεύ-

    <lb n="13"/>ξεως αὐτῶι ἐγκεκλή-

    <lb n="14"/>καμεν ἐπαναγκάσαι 

    <lb n="15"/>αὐτὸν τὸ δίκαιον 

    <lb n="16"/>ἡμῖν ὑποσχεῖν. τού-

    <lb n="17"/>του γὰρ γενομένου 

    <lb n="18"/>οὐ τὸν πλείω χρόνον 

    <lb n="19"/>καταφθαρησόμεθα, ἀλλὰ 

    <lb n="20"/>διὰ σὲ τῆς πάσης φιλαν-

    <lb n="21"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="high">θρωπίας τευξόμεθα.</supplied> 

    <lb n="22"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="high">εὐτύχει.</supplied> </ab></div><div n="meta.7413" type="description" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><rs type="material" cert="high">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.7413" type="commentary" subtype="textDate" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><date type="textDate" notBefore="-0244" notAfter="-0222">244 - 222 v.Chr.</date></p></div><div n="meta.7413" type="commentary" subtype="general" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>Datierung nach der Amtszeit des Strategen Aphthonetos (PP I und VIII  236).</p></div><div n="meta.7413" type="commentary" subtype="mentionedDates" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><head>Erwähnte Daten</head></div><div n="meta.7413" type="bibliography" subtype="principalEdition" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><listBibl default="NO"><bibl type="publication" subtype="principal" default="NO"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Petr.</title><biblScope type="volume">2</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">12</biblScope><biblScope type="parts">3</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos" default="NO"><biblScope type="numbers">7413</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP" default="NO"><series>0007</series>; ; <biblScope type="numbers">12</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref type="Perseus" href="0007;;12" evaluate="all" from="ROOT" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.7413" type="bibliography" subtype="illustrations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.7413" type="bibliography" subtype="otherPublications" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><head>Andere Publikationen</head><listBibl default="NO"><bibl type="publication" subtype="other" default="NO">P.Petr. III 29 (c)</bibl><bibl type="publication" subtype="other" default="NO">P.Lond. III 529 descr.</bibl><bibl type="publication" subtype="other" default="NO">M.Chr. 12</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.7413" type="history"